7/30/99
  To do:
    - Wayne: find out all changes for using the new compilor
    - Try to make code substain
    - Move one-time initialization code to external memory
    - Add trap feature back

  Changes for new compiler 3.0:
    The old compiler will layout out struture elements so that they are all
    word-aligned.  In constrast, the new compilor will try to pack structure
    elements as much as possible.  Since the VLC code table definitions we
    used do not have word-alignment for some elements, the memory layouts will
    be different between old and new compilor, and hence we need to either
    modify the structure definition/code table, or the assembly code so
    they the match with each other.

    Changes:
      In defs.h: definition of VLC tab, DCTtab and MVAuxTable structures.
      const.c is splitted into two files: const1.c and const.c
      For those tables (eg. mba inc, MB modes) whose definitions have not been
      changed, the assembly code needs to be updated for the packed layout.

  Copied SCCS files of all .s60 codes from the ratemuxnew directory.
  Copied SCCS files of const.c and const1.c from the ratemuxnew directory.
  Update defs.h with the new structure definitions.

  Testing:
    SUN simulation works.
    C version of C6X code complies and links.
    Turned on assembly version of bit input/output routine.  The code compiled
    and linked successfully.

  Move initialization code to external memory
    - Need to modify prototype in tgt.h as INTERN
      => created local version of kernal code.
    - Move all functions in dpi.c to external memory, as well as pidBufInit().
      Saved about 3 KB.

  Feature enhancement
    - Added trap capability back as inline call.
    - Added pidbuf link check capability back as function call.
    - Added some assembly codes to speed up execution.

  More debugging:
    - increase reduction ratio => SUN simulation error!
    - Found a bug in parsing picture coding extension.
